# Project Layout

```
Index/
├── web/                    # Next.js 16 web app + API (localhost:3000)
│   ├── src/app/api/        # API routes (tags, patterns, upload)
│   ├── prisma/             # SQLite database, schema, seed
│   └── .env                # DATABASE_URL, FIGMA_API_TOKEN
├── figma-plugin/           # Figma plugin (design.index)
└── docs/                   # Reference component examples and setup guides
```

## Dev Server

Start: `cd web && npm run dev` (runs on port 3000)

Port 3000 is shared with the Figma plugin — do NOT start other servers on it.

## Key Facts

- Node.js >= 20 required (see `.node-version`)
- Database: SQLite via Prisma (`file:./dev.db`)
- CORS headers for `/api/*` configured in `web/next.config.ts`
